featured_question.question: Is my emotional support cat allowed inside with me?
featured_question.answer:
So unfortunately, due to state laws you would only be able to have your cat in the coffee house for a very brief moment. 
It is in violation of health codes etc. and the coffee house would be fined for allowing such violations. 
Please refer to the Texas State Food Establishment rules.
The good news is you and your cat would be allowed to openly dine out on the patio. Just go when the sun goes down so you two won't burn in this Houston humidity. 

But please go. The coffee is nothing short of AMAZING.

I hope this answers your question.

We ordered lattes, cafe de olla, chicken and corn tamales, marranito (piggy) and empanadas.

Honestly the food was very good.
The latte was delicious. And the marranito tasted well. Some places the marranito is hard or doesn't have flavor. This one tasted recently made.

My only complaint here was the price of the tamales. As a Hispanic person when I saw they charge $10 for ONE tamale I was taken back. I can get half a dozen for the same price that taste amazing.

Either way I ordered two because I'm a sucker for tamales with coffee. And they were good, thankfully. Because if I had paid $20 for two tamales and they tasted back I probably would have asked them for a refund out of principal.

The place is clean and quiet and was filled with millennials studying on their computers (typical heights area ambiance).

Overall I'd come again.

Native Coffee Co. is a small artisanal coffee roastery that has taken the coffee scene by storm with their exceptional espresso offerings. Nestled in the heart of a vibrant urban neighborhood, this family-owned business has developed a loyal following of coffee enthusiasts and connoisseurs.

What sets Native Coffee Co.'s espresso apart is their unwavering commitment to sourcing only the finest coffee beans from indigenous communities worldwide. By forging direct relationships with local farmers, they ensure that their beans are ethically and sustainably cultivated, supporting the livelihoods of those who tend the land. This philosophy not only delivers superior taste but also promotes fair trade and environmental stewardship.

The secret to their delightful espresso lies in the roasting process. Native Coffee Co.'s skilled artisans carefully hand-roast small batches of beans to perfection, achieving a harmonious balance between brightness and depth. The result is a bold and rich flavor profile, with notes of dark chocolate, caramel, and hints of ripe fruit.

Stepping into Native Coffee Co.'s cozy cafe is an immersive experience in itself. The aroma of freshly ground coffee fills the air as baristas expertly craft each cup with precision and passion. Whether you prefer a velvety smooth latte or a simple shot of espresso, their dedication to quality ensures a consistently exceptional coffee experience.

For coffee lovers seeking an ethically-sourced, soulful espresso with a story to tell, Native Coffee Co. stands as a beacon of excellence in the world of specialty coffee.

Quaint little coffee shop near Montrose and the fourth ward. It's a little easy to miss while driving as it's in between two other buildings, but look for the large banner (pictured) with Native Coffee logo on the black fence decorated in vines. Parking is also a little tricky. You go slightly past the coffee shop and turn right at the mechanic/body shop. There's free parking in that large parking lot on the right, despite the parking signs threatening to be towed (confirmed by the employee at Native Coffee). Once you walk in, there's a beautiful patio and inside you'll find a clean, small coffee shop that looks newly renovated. The worker was great and I think I might have spotted the owner in the back working on sandwiches. They have a great menu but went basic and got my usual ice vanilla latte. There's roughly 15 tables and plenty of space when I visited. Only downside is that there were only a few outlets I could spot, but not an issue while I was there. Looked like they had a lot of customers from the neighborhood and a few from the car shop.

Definitely check it out!
